Class NumberList

  • java.lang.Object
    • NumberList
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.lang.Iterable, java.util.Collection

    public class NumberList
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.util.Collection
    Note: Corrections have been made to the return types for both toArray() methods. (2015-10-13). An object of this class represents a number list, i.e., an ordered collection of integers, each of Java class Long, with duplicates permitted. Be sure to read the Java documentation on interface java.util.Collection.
